00:56:30.390 --> 00:56:34.180
do you potentially have to change the frequency and do it less often?

938
00:56:35.710 --> 00:56:39.430
For invasive screening tests, so thinking about colonoscopies or endometrial

939
00:56:39.450 --> 00:56:43.430
biopsies, if you have somebody with a reduced penetrance variant, are these

940
00:56:43.470 --> 00:56:47.270
invasive tests actually needed, or could we potentially switch this

941
00:56:47.290 --> 00:56:50.710
person over to a non-invasive screening test as an

942
00:56:50.770 --> 00:56:54.650
alternative? And additionally, can these tests be

943
00:56:54.720 --> 00:56:58.430
done at a later point, or can the interval between tests be longer?

944
00:57:00.130 --> 00:57:03.390
And then when we think about risk-reducing surgery, such as a

945
00:57:03.910 --> 00:57:07.190
hysterectomy with bilateral salpingo-oophorectomy,

946
00:57:07.750 --> 00:57:11.690
the question to ask there for a reduced penetrance variant carrier,

947
00:57:12.210 --> 00:57:15.850
is the surgery needed, or can you forgo surgery and instead

948
00:57:15.870 --> 00:57:18.830
actually do some sort of screening for this individual as well?

949
00:57:19.490 --> 00:57:22.770
And if you do move forward with surgery, can the surgery be performed later, or

950
00:57:22.830 --> 00:57:25.750
maybe the surgery doesn't need to be as extensive as

951
00:57:26.910 --> 00:57:29.550
someone that has a different variant in the gene.

952
00:57:30.850 --> 00:57:34.510
And just focusing in on these last two, because these are discussions that I think

953
00:57:34.570 --> 00:57:38.270
we have oftentimes with patients across the hereditary

954
00:57:38.310 --> 00:57:42.110
spectrum. But when you think about screening tests, the things that

955
00:57:42.150 --> 00:57:45.990
you're always highlighting to patients are that the benefits of screening

956
00:57:46.030 --> 00:57:49.490
compared to moving forward with a risk-reducing surgery is that, of course, you

957
00:57:49.550 --> 00:57:52.990
don't have to go through surgery, and you don't have any of the immediate or

958
00:57:53.030 --> 00:57:55.910
long-term risks associated with a risk-reducing surgery.

959
00:57:56.690 --> 00:57:59.970
But these individuals obviously still need to do the screening,

960
00:58:00.310 --> 00:58:04.030
and screening itself may have risks, and the cancer risks remain

